> That would be a pretty scary legal abuse, but I wouldn't put it past them.

For RICO to apply, there would have to be a pattern of racketeering
activity. If this was the first and only time such an illegal activity
occurred (if whatever was done was illegal), it would not fall under RICO.
This is at least what the Prof. in my Bus. Law class taught us about the
law.

Tom

BTW: RICO is a VERY scary law.

